  "prompt": "What are probing question that you will ask to the user for buying an AC?",
  "response": "Okay, let's break down the probing questions I'd ask a user looking to buy an AC. I'll categorize them to make it easier to follow. My goal is to understand their needs and recommend the best AC solution for them.\n\n**I. Understanding the Space & Environment:**\n\n*   **Room Size & Layout:**\n    *   \"What are the approximate dimensions of the room you want to cool (length x width x height)?\"\n    *   \"Is it a single room, or part of an open-plan living space?\"\n    *   \"Are there any large openings to other rooms?\"\n    *   \"How many windows are there in the room?\"\n    *   \"What direction do the windows face (North, South, East, West)?\" (This impacts sun exposure)\n    *   \"Are the windows single-pane or double-pane?\" (Insulation matters)\n    *   \"How well is the room insulated (walls, ceiling, floor)?\"\n    *   \"What is the typical ceiling height?\"\n\n*   **Usage & Occupancy:**\n    *   \"How often will the AC be used? (e.g., daily, only on hot days, specific times of day)\"\n    *   \"How many people typically occupy the room when the AC is running?\"\n    *   \"Are there any heat-generating appliances in the room (e.g., computers, servers, cooking equipment)?\"\n\n*   **Climate & Location:**\n    *   \"Where are you located geographically? (City, State/Region)\" (This helps gauge the typical climate)\n    *   \"What are the average high temperatures during the hottest months of the year?\"\n    *   \"Is the humidity typically high or low in your area?\"\n    *   \"Do you experience extreme temperature fluctuations?\"\n\n**II. User Preferences & Needs:**\n\n*   **Cooling Requirements:**\n    *   \"What is your desired temperature setting when the AC is running?\"\n    *   \"How quickly do you want the room to cool down?\"\n    *   \"Are there any specific areas in the room that need to be cooled more effectively?\"\n\n*   **Budget & Cost:**\n    *   \"What is your budget for the AC unit?\"\n    *   \"Are you also considering the long-term running costs (electricity bills)?\"\n    *   \"Are you interested in any energy-efficient models, even if they have a higher upfront cost?\"\n\n*   **Features & Functionality:**\n    *   \"Are you interested in any specific features, such as a timer, sleep mode, remote control, or smart home integration?\"\n    *   \"Do you need a unit with a heating function as well (heat pump)?\"\n    *   \"How important is noise level to you?\"\n    *   \"Do you have any allergies or sensitivities that might require an air purifier function?\"\n    *   \"Are you looking for a portable, window, or split system AC?\"\n    *   \"Do you have any preferences regarding brand?\"\n\n*   **Installation & Maintenance:**\n    *   \"Are you planning to install the AC yourself, or will you need professional installation?\"\n    *   \"Are there any restrictions on installing an outdoor unit (e.g., in an apartment complex)?\"\n    *   \"How comfortable are you with routine maintenance tasks (e.g., cleaning filters)?\"\n\n**III. Existing Infrastructure & Limitations:**\n\n*   **Electrical Capacity:**\n    *   \"Do you know the electrical capacity of the circuit you plan to use for the AC?\" (Important for preventing overloads)\n    *   \"Are there any other high-power appliances on the same circuit?\"\n\n*   **Window Type & Size (for window units):**\n    *   \"What type of windows do you have (e.g., sliding, casement, double-hung)?\"\n    *   \"What are the dimensions of the window opening?\"\n\n*   **Space for Outdoor Unit (for split systems):**\n    *   \"Where would you plan to place the outdoor unit of a split system?\"\n    *   \"Are there any obstructions or limitations in that location?\"\n\n**IV. Uncovering Hidden Needs & Addressing Concerns:**\n\n*   \"Is there anything else that is important to you that we haven't discussed yet?\"\n*   \"Have you had any prior experience with AC units? If so, what did you like or dislike?\"\n*   \"Do you have any concerns about installing or using an AC unit?\"\n*   \"What are you hoping to achieve by purchasing this AC unit (e.g., better sleep, increased comfort, improved productivity)?\"\n\n**Why These Questions Are Effective:**\n\n*   **Specificity:** They avoid vague answers and provide concrete information.\n*   **Comprehensive:** They cover all relevant aspects, from room size to personal preferences.\n*   **Open-ended:** Many questions encourage the user to elaborate and reveal important details.\n*   **Customer-centric:** They focus on understanding the user's individual needs and priorities.\n\nBy asking these probing questions, you can gather the necessary information to recommend the most suitable AC unit for the user's specific situation, ensuring their satisfaction and a positive buying experience. Remember to listen carefully to the answers and adapt your questions as needed. Good luck!\n",
